[{"id":"VR871121","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows an energy level diagram of an atom. The diagram has four levels labeled, from top to bottom, 0 electron volts, negative 1 electron volt, negative 7 electron volts, and negative 9 electron volts. A note states that the figure is not drawn to scale.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR871121.g02.svg\"/></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The diagram shows the energy levels of a hypothetical atom with a ground-state energy of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"negative 9 electron volt\"><math alttext=\"negative 9 electron volt\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mo>−</mo><mn>9</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>eV</mtext></math></span></span>. The atom is excited to the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"negative 1 electron volt\"><math alttext=\"negative 1 electron volt\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>eV</mtext></math></span></span> energy level and then makes two separate transitions, emitting two photons. Which of the following could be the energy of one of the two photons?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR871121_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1 electron volt\"><math alttext=\"1 electron volt\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>eV</mtext></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 electron volts\"><math alttext=\"2 electron volts\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>eV</mtext></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4 electron volts\"><math alttext=\"4 electron volts\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>4</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>eV</mtext></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"8 electron volts\"><math alttext=\"8 electron volts\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>8</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>eV</mtext></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":1}]